      • process

        public Map<org.bouncycastle.asn1.ASN1ObjectIdentifier,​org.bouncycastle.asn1.x509.Extension> process​(X509Certificate[] requestCertificates,
                                                                                                          String remoteAddress,
                                                                                                          String remoteHost,
                                                                                                          X509Certificate cert,
                                                                                                          org.bouncycastle.cert.ocsp.CertificateStatus status,
                                                                                                          InternalKeyBinding internalKeyBinding)
        Description copied from interface: OCSPExtension
        Called by OCSP responder when the configured extension is found in the request.
        Specified by:
        process in interface OCSPExtension
        Parameters:
        requestCertificates - A certificate array from the original HttpServletRequest, used for authorization.
        remoteAddress - Extracted from the HttpServletRequest.
        remoteHost - DEPRECATED. Currently set to the same as remoteAddress. An extension that relies on this value must perform the remote lookup by itself.
        cert - X509Certificate the caller asked for in the OCSP request
        status - CertificateStatus the status the certificate has according to the OCSP responder, null means the cert is good
        internalKeyBinding - Used to get the trusted ca cert etc.
        Returns:
        Hashtable with X509Extensions <String oid, X509Extension ext> that will be added to responseExtensions by OCSP responder, or null if an error occurs
